  "title": "Healthcare Support Worker / Home Personal Care Aide (Flexible)",
  "description": "<p>This role involves providing <strong>companionship and basic care </strong>to an elderly individual in a home environment. You will engage the senior in meaningful activities, ensure their safety, and assist with daily living tasks. This is a part-time position ideal for candidates with prior caregiving experience seeking flexible work.<br /></p><p>(1) Companionship & Supervision – Spend time interacting with the senior, preventing loneliness and ensuring they stay safe (e.g., prevent fall risks). <br />(2) Assist with Activities of Daily Living – e.g. remind to take medicine, prepare light meals, help with mobility from bed to chair as needed. <br />(3) Engage in Exercises & Activities – lead the senior in simple stretching or hand exercises, and keep their mind active with conversation, simple games, or reminiscing<br /></p><p><em>Prior experience in caregiving or healthcare (e.g. ex-nurse, healthcare assistant, or having cared for an elderly family member) is </em><em><strong>required. </strong></em><em>Basic training in eldercare or certification (like WSQ in caregiving) </em><em><strong>preferred</strong></em>; <em>Must be Singapore Citizen or PR (role is not open to work pass holders)</em>; <em>Fluent in English, able to speak in Chinese, Malay or Dialects is an advantage for client interaction. </em></p>",
